title: Man Utd transfer news: Wayne Rooney’s agent jets into China in bid to seal lucrative move | Metro News
text:
Wayne Rooney’s agent jets into China in bid to seal lucrative transfer move gossip Louis Sealey for Metro.co.uk Wednesday 22 Feb 2017 9:56 pm Wayne Rooney could leave Manchester United before the end of next week (Picture: Getty) 
Wayne Rooney’s agent has flown to China in a bid to seal the Manchester United star a lucrative transfer move, reports say. 
England international Rooney is believed to have been told that he can leave United after spending 13 years at Old Trafford. Keep smiling! Mourinho of all people melts hearts with touching message to Ranieri 
The Daily Mirror say agent Paul Stretford arrived in Beijing this week and is ready to take internal flights to talk to clubs interested in his client. 
The Chinese Super League transfer window closes on Tuesday and Stretford is said to be in contact with a host of interested parties. 
Despite not being a regular under Jose Mourinho at United this season, Chinese clubs are understood to be prepared to offer Rooney around £600,000-a-week to secure his services. 
Rooney, 31, has scored 250 goals for the Red Devils since signing for the club in 2004 from Everton. Manchester United fixtures
